      • getCachedValueUnsafe

        Object getCachedValueUnsafe()
        Get current cache value or null.

        Warning: Do not use this method directly as it might expose arbitrary objects acting as a lock. Use Records.getCachedValue(Record) instead.

        Returns:
        current cached value or null or cached record mutex.

      • casCachedValue

        boolean casCachedValue(Object expectedValue,
                       Object newValue)
        Atomically sets the cached value to the given new value if the current cached value == the expected value.
        Parameters:
        expectedValue - the expected cached value
        newValue - the new cached value
        Returns:
        true if successful. False return indicates that the actual cached value was not equal to the expected cached value.
